Package sample.LoginSystem

Class UserSession

java.lang.Object
sample.LoginSystem.UserSession
public final class UserSession
extends java.lang.Object
Singleton class which instance is created when user has successfully logged into system. Instance of this class holds information about logged user and his privileges
Version:
1.0.1 29/05/2021
Author:
Daniel Czyz

    • getInstance

      public static UserSession getInstance​(int id, java.lang.String username, java.lang.String firstname, java.lang.String lastname, java.lang.String position, int[] privileges)
      Static method, when called and there is no instance of this class yet it creates one by executing constructor and then returns it, if there already exists one it does nothing but returns previously created instance
      Parameters:
      id - user id in database
      username - username assigned to user in database
      firstname - firstname assigned to user in database
      lastname - lastname assigned to user in database
      position - position assigned to user in database
      privileges - privileges assigned to user in database
